&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make is the platform to manage all your automations and AI agents in one visual landscape – for teams driving business impact without relying on developers. Part of Celonis, a global leader in process intelligence recognized on the Forbes Cloud 100 for seven consecutive years, we&#39;re headquartered in Prague, Czechia, with hubs in Madrid, Munich, Raleigh, and Pristina, and teams across the UK, France, India, and the Netherlands, among other locations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h4&gt;The Role&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an ambitious sales professional who is eager to learn &amp;amp; accelerate their career in sales. You&#39;ll work closely with experienced Account Executives and sales leaders while developing the skills required to progress into senior sales roles like: Solution Engineering, Account Executive or Partnerships.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;The Team&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;isSelectedEnd&quot;&gt;You’ll join a growing international sales team based in Madrid, working closely with other team members to expand Make.com’s presence across global markets.&amp;nbsp;The team focuses on enterprise outbound sales, building strong opportunities, and driving new pipeline through proactive prospecting.&amp;nbsp;You’ll collaborate across regions such as Spain, LATAM, Australia and Brazil (depending on language skills), in a culture built on ownership, curiosity, teamwork, and a strong sales mindset.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prospect &amp;amp; Engage – Identify and connect with strategic business accounts through cold calls, email, LinkedIn, and other outbound strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive Pipeline Growth – Generate new sales opportunities and schedule qualified meetings for AEs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand &amp;amp; Educate – Become a subject matter expert in automation and integration to effectively communicate Make.com’s value to potential customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Targeting – Research and develop personalized outreach strategies to engage decision-makers at top prospect accounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize &amp;amp; Track Progress – Maintain an organized book of business and consistently track engagement using CRM tools like Salesforce and HubSpot.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What We’re Looking For:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;📈 1+ years of experience in sales, business development, or a SaaS/tech environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;💬 &lt;strong&gt;Fluent Spanish and strong English communication skills&lt;/strong&gt; (written and verbal) are required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🇵🇹 Portuguese is a strong advantage, as it allows coverage of additional markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🌍 &lt;strong&gt;Comfortable working with international markets and adapting to different cultures and time zones (LATAM &amp;amp; Australia, etc.)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;📞 Not afraid to pick up the phone – you enjoy proactive outreach and speaking with new people.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;⚡ High energy &amp;amp; self-motivation – you thrive in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🧩 Business mindset – you understand how companies operate and can identify customer needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🕐 Strong time management &amp;amp; prioritization skills – ability to handle multiple outreach campaigns simultaneously.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🚀 Driven to succeed – you take initiative, are proactive, and want to be part of a high-growth company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;What we offer:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;📝 RSUs grant in a rapidly growing company raising its value every day&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;💸 Annual bonus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🌎 Multinational team with 42 nationalities creating the future of automation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;🎓 Learning &amp;amp; Development plan (online language, professional courses, conference tickets and other trainings) &amp;amp; 2 Company Learning Da

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Make is the platform to manage all your automations and AI agents in one visual landscape – for teams driving business impact without relying on developers. Part of Celonis, a global leader in process intelligence recognized on the Forbes Cloud 100 for seven consecutive years, we&#39;re headquartered in Prague, Czechia, with hubs in Madrid, Munich, Raleigh, and Pristina, and teams across the UK, France, India, and the Netherlands, among other locations.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3&gt;The Team&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Revenue Programs &amp;amp; Projects team is a core, strategic function within Make&#39;s global Revenue Organization. Our mission is to build a world-class, AI-led revenue operations engine — one that uses AI throughout to increase revenue per seller, eliminate administrative overhead, and give every rep and manager the tools they need to win consistently. This role reports to the Director of Revenue Programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a Revenue Programs GTM Engineer to work as the technical backbone of our Revenue Programs &amp;amp; Projects team. This is a hands-on, high-impact role for someone who thinks in systems, builds in Clay and Make, and gets energized by connecting technical work directly to sales outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will own the AI and automation infrastructure that powers our entire GTM motion — from end-to-end data enrichment pipelines and AI-driven outreach personalization to sales coaching agents, forecasting tools, and the internal toolbox that lets the Revenue Programs team ship faster. Unlike roles focused solely on data or process, you will be both the architect and the builder: designing systems that work at scale, then executing them with precision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is for someone who takes full ownership of their initiatives and measures success not by what was launched, but by what was adopted and what moved the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Areas of Responsibility&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Enrichment &amp;amp; CRM Data Quality&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full ownership of the data enrichment lifecycle within Salesforce and Snowflake. You will architect and maintain end-to-end pipelines, utilizing Clay and AI, while managing campaign operations, credit budgeting, and re-enrichment logic. A critical component involves partnering with cross-functional teams like RevOps and Data to audit data accuracy, resolve field-level conflicts, and ensure Salesforce remains reliable for reporting and analytics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;AI Agent Development &amp;amp; Automation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibility for engineering the team&#39;s AI ecosystem, ranging from building sales-specific tools like call scorecards and forecasting automations to managing the personalization infrastructure that drives outreach. A major focus is maintaining the &quot;Revenue Programs MCP Toolbox&quot;, a library of reusable AI tools and Make scenarios, to accelerate the wider team&#39;s delivery. You will also oversee the critical context infrastructure (version control and governance) that powers these agents and serve as the technical lead across all revenue programs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Efficiency &amp;amp; AI Adoption&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Responsibility for driving sales efficiency by ensuring the adoption of your AI tools, leading their implementation with sales leadership, automating repetitive tasks, and continuously monitoring their performance using data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration &amp;amp; Program Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lead high-impact, cross-functional initiatives from concept to adoption, focusing on tangible business outcomes rather than just delivery. You will provide technical support to program manage

